    {
      "text": "Monkey Puncher (さるパンチャー, Saru Panchā) is a video game for the Game Boy Color, developed by Atelier Double, and released in December 2000. The game's goal is to train a monkey to fight in organised boxing matches in order to save the main character's father and sibling.",
